[I] Virtual console locker

[T] vlock locks virtual consoles, as well as normal TTYs. It can prevent
[T] console-switching, and it supports PAM authentication by default.

[U] http://freshmeat.net/projects/vlock/

[A] Michael K. Johnson <johnsonm@redhat.com>
[A] Frank Benkstein <frank-vlock@benkstein.net>
[M] Rene Rebe <rene@t2-project.org>

[C] extra/shell
[F] CROSS

[L] GPL
[S] Stable
[V] 2.2.3

[D] e8fbcdd587a30f1805b32663ffb416739509c4e7a16b5aa5c2e795e8 vlock-2.2.3.tar.gz !https://repo.or.cz/vlock.git/snapshot/10b4f15701d3cbe9fe3d794af4132663aaea52d3.tar.gz

pkginstalled pam || var_append confopt ' ' --disable-pam
var_append makeopt ' ' 'vlock'
makeinstopt=
hook_add postmake 5 'cp -fv vlock $root$bindir'
hook_add postmake 5 'cp -fv man/*.1 $root$mandir/man1/'
hook_add postmake 5 'cp -fv man/*.8 $root$mandir/man8/'
hook_add postmake 5 'cp -fv man/*.5 $root$mandir/man5/'
